A vintage-style technical illustration showing an intricate family tree of mechanical brass clockwork boxes connected by ornate copper pipes and tubes, viewed from a three-quarter angle. Each box varies in size and contains tiny spinning gears visible through glass panels. The pipes branch upward and outward in an organic yet structured pattern, some splitting into multiple paths, others merging together. The background is aged parchment with subtle sepia tones. Warm amber light glows from within each connected box, creating a sense of living data flowing through the system. Small brass plates are mounted on each box but left deliberately blank. The overall composition suggests both rigid hierarchy and flexible interconnection, with a steampunk aesthetic that evokes Victorian engineering diagrams.
